\n<Female>The name of this town is "Drine." It means sinkhole. A hole
that suddenly appeared due to the ground collapsing. That's
how this town came to be inside it.

\n<Female>Above this town live the upper class, and people like us,
the lower class, survive on the scraps they throw away.

\n<Female>This is where those who have lost their way end up,
swallowed up like into a drain. All sorts of schemes and
desires swirl around here.

\n<Female>It seems that Ladro-chan has gone missing. Well,
disappearances are common in this town... but for someone to
go missing from the orphanage of all places.

\n<Female>I'm not exactly in a position to offer much help myself...
but it's just so pitiful.

\n<Female>If you can spare the time, please do visit the orphanage, or
donate some food or money.

\n<Grandpa>I've taken lodging in the noble district, so going up and
down is quite tough. It's harsh on this old body.

\n<Grandpa>The head of the family is furious. If it's discovered that
I've been overlooking this, I might be beheaded. Please
persuade them if that happens.

\n<Grandpa>Right now, everyone in the mansion is searching for the two
of you. Well, they'd never imagine you're in Drine, so
there's no worry of being found.

\n<Grandpa>How did I know you were here? Well, as your tutor, I see
right through both of your thoughts.

\n<Grandpa>However, my body can't keep up anymore... It took quite some
time to get here. It took about six days by carriage, with
plenty of rest.

\n<Grandpa>\n[8], did you really come all this way in one night? No
matter how high your physical abilities and the blessing of
the wind... my, my. You're practically a monster.

\n<Grandpa>It seems beastmen are rare around here. I've only seen an
elderly tanuki. I'm an old dog myself.

\n<Grandpa>I should have dressed more shabbily. The residents of the
slums are giving me quite the look.

\n<Grandpa>I'm well-versed in self-defense, so there's no problem if
I'm attacked. Still robust in my old age. Though I do have a
bit of joint pain.

\n<Grandpa>I won't enter the Adventurers' Guild. It would be
troublesome if your identities were questioned. I'll just
loiter around here.

\n<Grandpa>That vase was a gift from the head of the family two
generations ago. We were close in age, and he treated me
like a friend... He was a bright person, like Miss Chelsea.

\n<Grandpa>That it was broken by \n[8] might have been some sort of
divine revelation. I take it as a message from two
generations ago.

\n<Grandpa>\n[8], you use "Cat's Paw" in battle, but originally it's
meant to assist with writing documents and such. It's a
magic used by the executive branch.

\n<Grandpa>There's a saying, "even a cat's hand is desired," right?
That's where it comes from. It's that venerable a magic.

\n<Grandpa>I am watching over the growth of you two. But since you left
home on your own, I won't lend a hand. My hands, that is.
